<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<!--Below;This page contains an image and a button.We are going to use JS through the button to change the image that is being displayed to a different one.This is possible by changing the src value>
   <title> Changing Image Display using JS </title>
</head>
<body>
<!--Below;This is an image element that displays a.  We have assigned the image an ID named 'image' >
   <img src="images/sunflower.png" id="image" />
<!--Below;on clicking the button below the JS function named 'myFunc()' gets executed>
   <button type="button" onclick="myFunc()"> Change Image </button>
<!--Below;This is the JS Script.Here I created a function,the function goes to the document then gets the image element by the assigned Id then it changes the image src>
   <script>
      function myFunc() {
         document.getElementById("image").src = "images/star.png";
      }
   </script>
</body>
</html>
